The paper deals with Multi-objective Reinforcement Learning (MORL) and the use of a Gaussian process to interpolate the optimal value function over the reward function weights. This involves machine learning techniques and optimization, which are typically covered in the categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The application of this technique to the domain of autonomous vehicles suggests that it may also be relevant to the categories of cs.RO (Robotics) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the use of a Gaussian process for interpolation suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the category of cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems).
